  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Qsite Ticket Status provides an easy way for your customers to check their ticket status. The ticket status page shows a summary of the ticket, the current status of the ticket, the balance due, and when it was last updated. Users can send customers a link to Qsite when sending outgoing notifications.</p><h3 id=\"AutomatedNotifications:AddaQsite\u2122TicketStatusLink-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933246465/Automated+Notification+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933246465\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Automated Notification Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933803736/Send+an+SMS+Ticket+Status+Notification\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933803736\" data-linked-resource-version=\"11\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Sending an SMS Notification to a Customer</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936523327/Qsite+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936523327\" data-linked-resource-version=\"14\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qsite\u2122 Resources</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936851025/image-20230607-183525.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"AutomatedNotifications:AddaQsite\u2122TicketStatusLink-SendanAutomatedNotificationwithaQsiteTicketStatusLink\">Send an Automated Notification with a Qsite Ticket Status Link</h2><p /><p>1. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Location Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936851025/image-20230607-183530.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Settings Overview screen, click the <strong>Communications</strong> dropdown on the left column of the list of settings. From the list of options, click <strong>Notifications</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936851025/image-20230607-183539.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. On the Notification Automation Overview page, you can add a new notification by clicking <strong>Create Notification Automation</strong> or add this link to an existing notification by clicking the <strong>Edit button</strong> under the Actions column.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936851025/image-20230607-183545.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>4. For this example, we are creating a new notification. On the New Automation Notification screen, begin filling out applicable fields.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936851025/image-20230607-183556.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>Notification</strong> <strong>Name</strong> - Give your Automated Notification a name to identify its purpose.</p></li><li><p><strong>Location</strong> - Select whether this notification is strictly for your location or all locations (if applicable).</p></li><li><p><strong>Trigger</strong> - Qsite status shortcodes are available when selecting either Ticket Notification or Ticket Status Change.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Ticket</strong> <strong>Notification</strong> - The notification is sent out manually when clicking the notification button on the ticket. You can choose whether to send it via email or SMS.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ticket Status</strong> <strong>Change</strong> - The notification is automatically queued for delivery when the ticket is placed into the assigned status. Select the ticket status based on your preference for delivery timing.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Delivery</strong> - Select whether this notification will be delivered to the customer's email or via SMS.</p><ul><li><p>For SMS, the customer will need an assigned SMS Phone number and the appropriate carrier.</p></li></ul></li></ul><h3 id=\"AutomatedNotifications:AddaQsite\u2122TicketStatusLink-NotificationShortCodes\">Notification Short Codes</h3><p>Short Codes are dynamic values that change based on the context of your notification. Qsite Short Codes are available for any notification when selecting the triggers for <strong>Ticket Notification</strong> or <strong>Ticket Status Change</strong>.</p><p>After making your selections, click <strong>Save</strong> to update your changes and create the notification.</p><h3 id=\"AutomatedNotifications:AddaQsite\u2122TicketStatusLink-MessageSubject\">Message Subject</h3><p>Create a subject for your notification, similar to the subject of an email. You can enter any of the available shortcodes above to customize the available information.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936851025/image-20230607-183603.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"AutomatedNotifications:AddaQsite\u2122TicketStatusLink-SendTo\">Send To</h3><p>Copy/paste <strong>{customer}</strong> into this field, so the system knows this notification will be delivered to the customer assigned to the ticket.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936851025/image-20230607-183608.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"AutomatedNotifications:AddaQsite\u2122TicketStatusLink-SMSMessage\">SMS Message</h3><p>Add the message that will be communicated to the customer. To include a link to check their ticket status, make sure you include <strong>{ticket_status_url}</strong> somewhere in the message. This link will allow the customer to check their ticket status, plus additional information including balance due, customer-visible notes, and your store's contact information.\u00a0</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936851025/image-20230607-183614.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"AutomatedNotifications:AddaQsite\u2122TicketStatusLink-SMSNotificationExample\">SMS Notification Example</h3><p>Below is an example of the SMS that the customer will receive and the Qsite Ticket Status page on a mobile device.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936851025/image-20230607-183621.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936851025/image-20230607-183627.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.20.X</p>",
